---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="DaemonCore" description="The governance layer beneath multi-agent intelligence. Not an orchestrator. Not a framework. The OS-level foundation.">
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>DaemonCore</h1>
    <p class="hero-tagline">The governance layer beneath multi-agent intelligence.</p>
    <p class="hero-description">
      DaemonCore operates below orchestration. It defines what agents are allowed to do,
      enforces safety boundaries, and provides the structural foundation that orchestrators
      and frameworks build upon.
    </p>
    <div class="callout callout-important">
      <strong>Not an agent framework.</strong> Not an orchestrator. Not a workflow tool.
      DaemonCore is the OS-level governance layer that sits beneath all of these.
    </div>
    <div class="hero-cta">
      <a href="/daemon" class="btn-primary">Explore the Kernel</a>
      <a href="/daemon/what-it-is" class="btn-secondary">What Is This?</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title">Why Governance Beneath Orchestration?</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">
      Today's AI systems lack a governance layer. Orchestrators coordinate agents,
      but nothing enforces the rules they operate under. DaemonCore fills this gap.
    </p>
    <div class="grid grid-3">
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Safety by Architecture</h3>
        <p>
          Constraints are structural, not advisory. Agents cannot exceed their
          capability envelope. Boundaries are enforced at the system level.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Vendor Isolation</h3>
        <p>
          Different AI providers operate under unified governance. Switch models
          without restructuring. No cross-contamination of context or state.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Deterministic Foundation</h3>
        <p>
          Same inputs produce same behavior. Agents boot into consistent context.
          Predictability enables trust at scale.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-stack">
    <h2 class="section-title">The Stack</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">
      DaemonCore sits at the foundation. Everything else builds on top.
    </p>
    <div class="stack-diagram">
      <div class="stack-layer stack-applications">
        <span class="stack-label">Applications</span>
        <span class="stack-desc">Chat interfaces, automation tools, IDEs</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stack-layer stack-orchestration">
        <span class="stack-label">Orchestration</span>
        <span class="stack-desc">LangChain, CrewAI, AutoGen, custom frameworks</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stack-layer stack-governance">
        <span class="stack-label">Governance</span>
        <span class="stack-desc">DaemonCore â€” safety, boundaries, coordination</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stack-layer stack-models">
        <span class="stack-label">Models</span>
        <span class="stack-desc">Claude, GPT, Gemini, open-source LLMs</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title">Components</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">
      DaemonCore comprises modular subsystems. Each operates independently.
      Together, they form the governance foundation.
    </p>
    <div class="grid grid-3">
      <a href="/daemon" class="card card-interactive">
        <h3>Kernel</h3>
        <p>
          The core governance specification. Boot protocols, safety scaling,
          capability envelopes, and coordination rules.
        </p>
        <span class="badge badge-active">Active</span>
      </a>
      <div class="card coming-soon">
        <h3>SDK</h3>
        <p>
          Developer tooling for building DaemonCore-native agents
          and integrations.
        </p>
        <span class="badge">Pending</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card coming-soon">
        <h3>Hub</h3>
        <p>
          Central registry for agents, profiles, and shared governance
          configurations.
        </p>
        <span class="badge">Pending</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-early-access">
    <h2 class="section-title">Early Access</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">
      DaemonCore is in private development. We're selectively opening access
      to teams building production multi-agent systems.
    </p>
    <div class="ea-cta">
      <a href="/early-access" class="btn-primary">Register Interest</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="status">
    <h2>Status</h2>
    <p>
      Kernel specification stabilising. Core boot protocol and safety framework defined.
      Public specification available for review.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="https://github.com/stux-os/daemon-core-public" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View on GitHub</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .callout {
    background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.1);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    margin: var(--space-4) 0;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .callout-important {
    background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.1);
    border-left-color: #ef4444;
  }

  .section-stack {
    background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.05);
    padding: var(--space-6) var(--space-4);
    margin: var(--space-6) calc(-1 * var(--space-4));
  }

  .stack-diagram {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: var(--space-4) auto 0;
  }

  .stack-layer {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-amethyst);
    margin-bottom: -1px;
  }

  .stack-layer:first-child {
    border-radius: 8px 8px 0 0;
  }

  .stack-layer:last-child {
    border-radius: 0 0 8px 8px;
  }

  .stack-label {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .stack-desc {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .stack-applications {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
  }

  .stack-orchestration {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
  }

  .stack-governance {
    background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.2);
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    border-width: 2px;
  }

  .stack-governance .stack-label {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .stack-models {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .stack-layer {
      flex-direction: column;
      text-align: center;
      gap: var(--space-1);
    }
  }

  .section-early-access {
    background: rgba(247, 184, 1, 0.05);
    border: var(--border-width) solid var(--color-accent);
    padding: var(--space-5) var(--space-4);
    margin: var(--space-4) 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .ea-cta {
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
  }
</style>
